{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5b144745-3142-41af-933b-f1f299af91dd","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so I can't review your specific workflow. But here's exactly what you need to change to switch to **NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC)**:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Register your package on NuGet.org\n\nGo to **nuget.org → Manage Package → Trusted Publishers** and add a GitHub Actions publisher, specifying your repo owner, repo name, and (optionally) the environment name.\n\n### 2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow\n\n**a) Add `id-token: write` permission** so the runner can request an OIDC token:\n\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # required for trusted publishing\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**b) Replace the `dotnet nuget push` step.** Remove the API key and use `--source` with the trusted-publish endpoint:\n\n```yaml\n# BEFORE\n- name: Push to NuGet\n  run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n\n# AFTER\n- name: Install credential provider\n  uses: dotnet/setup-nuget-publish@v1   # sets up OIDC auth\n\n- name: Push to NuGet\n  run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nNo `--api-key` flag is needed — the credential provider handles auth via the OIDC token automatically.\n\n### 3. (Optional but recommended) Use a GitHub Environment\n\nIf you configured a specific environment name in the NuGet trusted publisher settings, add it to the job:\n\n```yaml\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    environment: nuget-publish   # must match what you registered\n```\n\n### 4. Clean up\n\nRemove `NUGET_API_KEY` from your repository secrets once the new flow is verified.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of changes:**\n| Area | Old | New |\n|------|-----|-----|\n| Auth | `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | OIDC token (automatic) |\n| Permission | not needed | `id-token: write` |\n| Workflow step | `--api-key` flag | `dotnet/setup-nuget-publish@v1` action |\n| NuGet.org config | API key | Trusted publisher registration |\n\nWould you like me to create or update a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"760dc098-2e4b-4ace-95ac-7ad57b2db70d","outputTokens":594},"id":"b430c493-bcc2-4467-a066-532e718fd48a","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:41:06.273Z","parentId":"66ae350f-19e3-4c28-bf1c-a744d0c41666"}
